**Summary**

Adds a test case demonstrating that `clone()` returns the same reference
for custom class instances that do not override `valueOf()`.

Currently, all objects have a default `valueOf()` implementation that returns `this`,
which prevents `cloneObject()` from being called. As a result, `clone()` does not
clone non-POJO objects.

This test documents the current behavior described in #12574.

**Examples**

```js
class MyClass {
  constructor(val) {
    this.val = val;
  }
}

const obj = new MyClass(42);
const cloned = clone(obj);

console.log(obj === cloned); // true
